{{Youmay|the real-world ''[[Star Wars]]'' author|Kaufman's [[in-universe]] [[Ryan Kaufman|namesake]]}}
A former continuity supervisor at [[LucasArts]], '''Ryan Kaufman''' worked on many games including [[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Mysteries of the Sith|''Mysteries of the Sith'']], ''[[Star Wars: Bounty Hunter]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: Republic Commando]]''. He collaborated closely with [[Karen Traviss]] in the writing of ''[[Republic Commando: Hard Contact]]'' and [[Republic Commando: Triple Zero|''Triple Zero'']], and co-authored the ''[[Guide to the Grand Army of the Republic]]'' with her. He wrote the [[Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures (graphic novels)|''Clone Wars Adventures'']] tales ''[[The Package (comic story)|The Package]]'', [[Orders (comic story)|''Orders'']] and ''[[Spy Girls]]''; wrote the short story [[The Tale of the Aiwha Pod (short story)|''The Tale of the Aiwha Pod'']]; and co-wrote ''[[Underworld: A Galaxy of Scum and Villainy]]'' with [[Abel G. Peña]].

